An important point to observe is the following. Given that  is fixed, 
-bundles are classified by . 
This gives one copy of  as the parameter space for inequivalent 
-bundles. 
We can now projectivise these Hilbert-space bundles into -bundles 
and still we are left with one copy of  as the 
parameter space. This differs from the  copies of 
found above. However there is no contradiction. The operations of projectivisation 
and classification of bundles over , call them  and , do not commute:
. In our approach we first construct a family of Hilbert-space 
bundles, classified by the elements of , then we projectivise 
them into -bundles. Therefore the correct order for these operations is 
, i.e. , first classify, then projectivise.


